Source: pg-dbms-errlog
Section: database
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Ruohang Feng <rh@vonng.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13), postgresql-all (>= 217~)
Standards-Version: 4.6.2
Rules-Requires-Root: no
Homepage: https://github.com/HexaCluster/pg_dbms_errlog

Package: postgresql-PGVERSION-pg-dbms-errlog
Architecture: any
Provides: postgresql-pg-dbms-errlog
Depends: ${postgresql:Depends}, postgresql-PGVERSION-pg-statement-rollback (>= 1.5), ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Oracle-style DML error logging for PostgreSQL PGVERSION
 pg_dbms_errlog lets DML continue after row errors and records failures in a
 dedicated error table. It uses shared memory and background workers together
 with pg_statement_rollback.
